<div id="content" lang="en" dir="ltr">
<strong><a class="nonexistent" href="./RedNaga">RedNaga</a></strong>: correct me if i'm wrong, but i thought the normal winning procedure was: 
    <ol type="1">

    <li>
<p>
Enter Angband lv99, where there should be Sauron, but <strong>no</strong> stairs down. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
Kill Sauron, so making the down staircase appear. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
Enter Angband lv100, to find Morgoth and <strong>no</strong> stairs down. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
Kill him, then do whatever you like. 
</p>
</li>

    </ol>


<p>
If so, than my character has been screwed really bad, because my procedure has been instead: 
</p>

    <ol type="1">

    <li>
<p>
Entered Angband lv99 and didn't find Sauron (i explored the whole level and had Vision at top level so i don't think i missed some hidden rooms), but found plenty of stairs down. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
After leaving and reentering lv99 a few times (to lv98, not 100), i finally find Sauron and kill him, but no stairs appear. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
Descent then into one of the pre-existing stairways, but no trace of Morgoth on lv100 (same as above) 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
Well... after entering and leaving lv100 a few times i run into a <strong>U</strong> lair and got killed... 
</p>
</li>

    </ol>


<p>
If that could matter, this was the same character who encountered Sauron on Mount Doom lv99 (<a href="./BugReport167">BugReport167</a>), but i didn't kill him there, used Destruction instead (bad keypress, in fact :(). 
</p>
<p>
<strong><a href="./NeilStevens">NeilStevens</a></strong>: See my explanation on <a href="./BugReport167">BugReport167</a>.  All that applies to this one, as well.  Thank you. 
</p>
